<TITLE>Hull councillor Steven Bayes suspended from practising as a nurse over 'allegation'</TITLE>


<TEXT>
One of Hull's most senior councillors has been <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE">suspended</EVENT> from <EVENT eid="e2" class="OCCURRENCE">practising</EVENT> as a nurse for <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DURATION" value="P18M">18 months</TIMEX3>.

Councillor Steven Bayes, who <EVENT eid="e3" class="OCCURRENCE">worked</EVENT> as an adult nurse at Hull Royal Infirmary, has been <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE">issued</EVENT> with an interim suspension order by the Nursing and Midwifery Council.

The NMC <EVENT eid="e5" class="OCCURRENCE">imposed</EVENT> the order on <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DATE" value="2017-12-06">December 6</TIMEX3>, <EVENT eid="e6" class="OCCURRENCE">suspending</EVENT> Cllr Bayes's registration as a nurse until <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DATE" value="2018-06">June 2018</TIMEX3> while an <EVENT eid="e7" class="OCCURRENCE">investigation</EVENT> into "an allegation" is carried out.

In its determination, the NMC <EVENT eid="e8" class="REPORTING">said</EVENT>: "Case examiners are yet to <EVENT eid="e9" class="OCCURRENCE">decide</EVENT> whether there is a case to <EVENT eid="e10" class="OCCURRENCE">answer</EVENT> in relation to the <EVENT eid="e11" class="OCCURRENCE">allegation made</EVENT> against you."

Cllr Bayes, who represents Orchard Park and Greenwood, has been a cabinet member since Labour <EVENT eid="e12" class="OCCURRENCE">retook</EVENT> control of the Guildhall in <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DATE" value="2012">2012</TIMEX3>. He was <EVENT eid="e13" class="OCCURRENCE">suspended</EVENT> by the Labour Party in <TIMEX3 tid="t5" type="DATE" value="2017-10">October</TIMEX3>, although reasons for his suspension have not been <EVENT eid="e14" class="OCCURRENCE">disclosed</EVENT>.

Although still a councillor, Cllr Bayes no longer holds the cabinet portfolio for visitor destination overseeing regeneration projects including . Council leader Steve Brady has <EVENT eid="e15" class="OCCURRENCE">taken</EVENT> on Cllr Bayes' cabinet responsibilities and <EVENT eid="e16" class="REPORTING">said</EVENT> the party suspension was being <EVENT eid="e17" class="OCCURRENCE">dealt</EVENT> with at a regional level. The interim order <EVENT eid="e18" class="OCCURRENCE">hearing</EVENT> was <EVENT eid="e19" class="OCCURRENCE">held</EVENT> by the NMC's <EVENT eid="e20" class="OCCURRENCE">investigating</EVENT> committee in London on <TIMEX3 tid="t6" type="DATE" value="2017-12-06">December 6</TIMEX3>.

Cllr Bayes, who has been <EVENT eid="e21" class="OCCURRENCE">registered</EVENT> as a nurse for <TIMEX3 tid="t7" type="DURATION" value="P32Y">32 years</TIMEX3>, was present at the <EVENT eid="e22" class="OCCURRENCE">hearing</EVENT> and was <EVENT eid="e23" class="OCCURRENCE">represented</EVENT> by legal counsel Andrew Jordan.

The NMC <EVENT eid="e24" class="REPORTING">say</EVENT> the panel can only <EVENT eid="e25" class="OCCURRENCE">impose</EVENT> an interim order if it <EVENT eid="e26" class="OCCURRENCE">finds</EVENT> it is necessary to <EVENT eid="e27" class="OCCURRENCE">protect</EVENT> the public, is in the public interest or in the registrant's interest.

A review of the order will <EVENT eid="e28" class="OCCURRENCE">take</EVENT> place in <TIMEX3 tid="t8" type="DURATION" value="P6M">six months</TIMEX3> and then every <TIMEX3 tid="t9" type="DURATION" value="P3M">three months</TIMEX3> and <TIMEX3 tid="t10" type="DATE" value="X">18</TIMEX3> months is the maximum period of time for an interim order.

The review <EVENT eid="e29" class="OCCURRENCE">hearing</EVENT> can <EVENT eid="e30" class="OCCURRENCE">continue</EVENT>, replace, <EVENT eid="e31" class="I_ACTION">vary</EVENT> the order or <EVENT eid="e32" class="OCCURRENCE">evoke</EVENT> it. If the case against Cllr Bayes is not <EVENT eid="e33" class="OCCURRENCE">concluded</EVENT> in <TIMEX3 tid="t11" type="DURATION" value="P18M">18 months</TIMEX3>, the NMC can <EVENT eid="e34" class="OCCURRENCE">apply</EVENT> to the High Court for an extension.

Cllr Bayes has been <EVENT eid="e35" class="OCCURRENCE">contacted</EVENT> for comment but has not yet <EVENT eid="e36" class="OCCURRENCE">responded</EVENT>.
</TEXT>


